1 hour ago, Dragon01 said:

I don't think there'll be much 3.75m in the Saturn revamp. Sizes will go up to be more realistic, and then Saturn I will be 4.375m. I think S-IV might be 3.75m elements, but it'll probably be the only part in that size.

Under standard BDB calculation, lower stage sizes for Saturn C-series are 4.375m (C-1, C-2), 5m (C-3, C-4), 6.25m (C-5) and 7.5m (C-8). We're talking big.  Even Saturn I, the smallest rocket in the series, uses a first stage that's second only to SLS and Shuttle-derived designs in diameter. 

Isn't BDB saturn I 3.75?

21 minutes ago, derega16 said:

Isn't BDB saturn I 3.75?

Right now it is, but the revamp will be larger. The current version is underscaled, because at the time it was made, @CobaltWolf was thinking that 6.25m was too large, and there were serious wobble issues with that, too. Since then, JNSQ came out, wobble has gotten better and @Nertea, among others, had since released perfectly usable 7.5m parts, pretty much rendering those concerns moot.  As such, the Saturn revamp will introduce proper scaling. This will fit much better with other parts, too, their proportions will be correct when used with Saturn rockets.
